&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Cancer Support Worker&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have the drive and passion for caring for patients at the end of life?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gateshead are proud to have launched a new Hospice at Home Service and we are looking for individuals to join this new team to provide one to one care in the patients own home. The service comprises of a dedicated team of experienced support workers, administration assistants and is led by 2 Band 6 Nurse Coordinator’s. This team form part of Gateshead NHS Foundation Trust Community Business Unit and has links to the Specialist Palliative Care Team who are hospital and community based.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In order to provide the best possible patient care, the Hospice at Home service is a joint venture with Gateshead Trust, Macmillan and Gateshead Commissioners with streamlined interfaces between different care settings. It is a service that includes caring for patients at home, ensuring that patients have choice and the opportunity to be cared for in the Right Place at the Right Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role of the support worker is to provide high standards of domiciliary care to the patient in their own home at the end of life. You will work closely with all other members of the multidisciplinary team, including District Nurses, GPs and MacMillan Nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have excellent communication skills , experience of working in a care setting and evidence of compassion and understanding of palliative care. Flexible working on occasion’s maybe required to meet with the demands of the service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to fluctuating demands these posts will be predominately part time between 22.5 and 30 hours per week. Shift patterns will range from 4 – 12 hours per day and may include split shifts and night shift.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicants will be required to attend an assessment day (Date to be arranged) with the opportunity to meet with other members of the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a car owner/driver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Candidates will be subject to an enhanced DBS Check and must be eligible to work in the UK.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact Name for informal discussions&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tracey Cowper Clinical Operational Manager or Nicola Allen Clinical Lead Community Serviceson 0191 4455131&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Gateshead Health NHS Foundation Trust is committed to providing a working environment free from harassment and discrimination, where there is equality of opportunity and individual differences are valued and respected.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For information on other vacancies please visit: NHS jobs&lt;/p&gt;
